== Ubuntu & Debian

sudo apt-get install libxml2-dev libxslt1-dev zlib1g-dev ruby1.8-dev build-essential ruby ruby1.8 rubygems
sudo gem install pkg/riddl.gem

== Others

find out yourself

== Gem Dependencies

You don't need to care about them, as they will be automatically installed
during the installation of the riddl.gem. Here is a list of them just in case
you are interessted:

* ruby-xml-smart (>= 0.2.1.1 needed)
* rack
* thin 
* mime-types
* eventmachine (>= 1.0.0.beta.4')
* em-websocket

If you are interessted in writing websocket clients we recommend

* em-websocket-client (there is no examples included for this)
